[SN]TITLE[SN]
Rathfriland pensioner tied up by armed burglars

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man in his 70s has been tied up by armed men during a burglary at his home in Rathfriland, County Down.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The burglars, who are believed to have had a gun, entered the pensioner's home at Banbridge Road some time between 07:00 and 08:00 GMT on Tuesday.
One of the men was wearing a balaclava. They tied the victim's feet with a belt before stealing money.
Police said the pensioner was not injured but had been left badly shaken by the "terrifying ordeal".
